text: Our regular place for snacks. Food is reasonably good. They have pretty good process normally dont take ling to order and pay. We like their Cheese Chicken sausage and Sotong sticks. They also introduce new items here and there which is great for us.

Very tasty hot curry puff.
There is a stand-up dining table right next to this stall.
Dry mee siam. Can't taste its tangy, sweet, sour favour. It's missing. There's room for improvement. With little mee siam gravy, good to have that drooling.

Easy to eat snacks! There are lots of variant to try. I love the cheese fish stick so much, it's so soft and yummy ❤️ not a big fans of the gyoza since the vegetable tastes stronger than the meat

The staff is very kind and helpful

The stall is for takeaway only, but there is a table just opposite the store.

They currently are serving rojak as a SG60 special. The rojak sauce was excellent — it was not overly sweet and had the fragrance from the torch ginger flower. In it, there were chunks of you tiao, tau pok, tempeh, and cucumber. It was also topped with peanuts.
